@lexfridmam i feel in this "end of humanity" thought experiment the problem to solve might not be alignment. 
I believe you can't have perfect alignment of any being (certainly not a human or group of humans and I doubt any HGI) with humanity's best interests. The obvious issue i see is allowing ultimate power to be yielded by any single decision making system. Even if someone claims in the future that alignment has been achieved it would not be certain and we would still have the same debates.
The only way to not be at the mercy of a powerful HGI might be through hard limits to its access, power, or having the power to defeat it (which will likely not be possible).

